0 Okay , ' enjoy ' is a pretty relative term , but flexibility is in order when you 're dealing with a filmmaker of James Glickenhaus ' calibre.<br /><br />McBain is truly one of the most ridiculous , over the top action films I 've ever seen , without the nasty edge of The Exterminator . Other reviews have commented on a suspension of disbelief regarding the film 's heroic middle aged commandos , but how about making a film in the Philippines that is set in Colombia ? All the extras are Filipino . In fact the only character who looks remotely Hispanic is good ol' Victor Argo as the much reviled ' El Presidente ' ! Oh yes , we also have Maria Conchita Alonso overemoting like crazy as a rebel leader . There are tons of explosions and bodies flying everywhere in this amusing paean to the glories of American imperialism .
