0 The novelty of hearing clean - cut Jay Leno spout four - letter words is the only memorable aspect of this formulaic mismatched - police - partners caper . In COLLISION COURSE , the pelican - faced comedian teams up with the late Pat Morita to track down a stolen prototype turbocharger ( think car lover Leno played a hand in the plot ? ) . The two leads try hard , they really do , but Leno is no actor and Morita 's fish - out - of - water routine gets old in a hurry . The film carries a bit of cheesy ' 80s appeal , but its worthy moments become increasingly scarce as it fills out its overlong 100-minute running time . Fans of Leno 's considerable comedic talents will feel let down ; everyone else will just be bored .
