0 This kind of film has become old hat by now , has n't it ? The whole thing is syrupy nostalgia turned in upon itself in some kind of feedback loop.<br /><br />It sure sounds like a good idea : a great ensemble cast , some good gags , and some human drama about what could have / might have been . Unfortunately , there is no central event that binds them all together , like there was in " The Big Chill " , one of those seminal movies that spawned copycat films like this one . You end up wanting to see more of one or two particular people instead of getting short takes on everyone . The superficiality this creates is not just annoying , it 's maddening . The below - average script does n't help .
